<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
Maur:  What exactly does armor class do? <p>
Does it decrease the damage you take or make monsters miss more often or what? 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a>: <a class="interwiki" title="Self" href="./Documentation/Characteristics"><img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/moin-inter.png" alt="[Self]" height="16" width="16">See the documentation on armor class</a>. Granted, we need to make that easier to find. <img src="./wiki/rightsidebar/img/smile.png" alt=":)" height="15" width="15"> 
</p>
<p>
On a re-read of that, I think we may need a spoiler on AC, or else expand the doc. Anyway... a monster's to-hit is affected by AC. 
</p>
<p>
Maur: thx. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./MassimilianoMarangio">MassimilianoMarangio</a>: AC (max. 150) also lowers the melee damage of monsters (HURT or SHATTER attacks only). The damage is reduced by damage * AC / 250, i.e. with an AC of at least 150 the damage is only 2/5. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./GrootheWanderer">GrootheWanderer</a>:  Does the usefulness of AC really top out at 150.  This would mean my AC 200+ tank melee characters should be using helms with more useful stat and resistance bonuses instead of that nice little helm with the huge AC. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Armor Class also afefcts the frequency and strength of your critical hits, the higher AC, the better. 
</p>
<p>
<a href="./NerdanelVampire">NerdanelVampire</a>: Now that's... unintuitive. I think it hasn't been documented anywhere either. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: It's also wrong.  Never mind, heh. 
</p>
